  "author_association": "MEMBER",
  "body": "Currently it is possible to have the following race condition:\r\n\r\n1. You have a custom token controller that acts on secrets when SAs are created (like the `TokensController`)\r\n2. `ControllerClientBuilder` is used to build a SA for some controller\r\n3. Both `TokensController` and the custom token controller create secrets for the SA\r\n4. `ControllerClientBuilder` sees the secret for the SA, and starts the controller it was building\r\n5. Both `TokensController` and the custom token controller try to update the SA and conflict\r\n6. `TokensController` fails the update, and decides to delete the secret because of the conflict\r\n7. The controller built by `ControllerClientBuilder` is now broken because its secret was deleted\r\n\r\nIt should be possible to fix the `TokensController` so that it is reentrant and does not try to delete secrets on conflict errors.\r\n\r\ncc @liggitt @deads2k \r\n\r\nSeen in https://github.com/openshift/origin/pull/13579#issuecomment-291219349",
